   validif (hero.childfound[cHelpClr].field[cClrNeutGE].value = 0)
   validif (hero.childfound[cHelpMys].field[cClrTurn].value = 2)
   validif (hero.childfound[cPalTurnUn].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0)]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSpellDrai" name="Spell Drain" description="You can cast any spell that you drain from a creature&#146;s mind.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Cha 15, energy drain supernatural ability, Improved Energy Drain, caster level 5th.\n\n{b}Benefits{/b}: If you bestow a negative level upon a spellcasting creature, and that creature loses a prepared spell, you gain the ability to cast that spell once (as if you had prepared it). Treat the spell&#146;s effect as if it had been cast by the character who prepared it (including caster level, save DC, and so forth). You need not have the requisite ability score to cast the spell (for instance, you need not have an Intelligence of 13 or higher to cast a {i}fireball{/i} drained from the mind of a wizard).\n\nThe spell remains in your mind for up to 1 hour. You can have a maximum number of stolen spells equal to your Charisma bonus (minimum 1); any spells that you would gain above this number are simply lost.\n\nThis feat has no effect on spellcasters who don&#146;t prepare spells (such as a sorcerer, who simply loses one spell slot for each negative level bestowed as normal) or who have no spells prepared (such as a fighter, or a wizard who has cast all her spells)." compset="Feat" summary="If neg level drains prepared spell, can use during next hr (max X)." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Monstrous"/>
    <eval phase="Render"><![CDATA[
   var bonus as number
   bonus = hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value
   field[xSumm].text = "If neg level drains prepared spell, can use during next hr (max " & bonus & ")."]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Energy drain ability required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[xEnergyDra].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Improved Energy Drain required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fImpEneDra] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 5th required."><![CDATA[herofield[tMaxCaster].value >= 5]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Charisma 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aCHA].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSpurnDeTo" name="Spurn Death&apos;s Touch" description="You can channel divine energy to remove some of the harmful effects of attacks made by undead creatures.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Ability to turn undead.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action that does not provoke attacks of opportunity, you can spend one of your turning attempts for the day to touch an ally to heal 1d4 points of ability damage, remove a paralysis effect, or remove a negative level. You can only use this effect to heal ability damage dealt by an undead creature or remove effects caused by an undead creature." compset="Feat" summary="Stand, use 1 turn, touch heals 1d4 ability dam/neg level/paralysis from undead." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)

Adjust for Paladin Level (Done)

Test?</comment>
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Divine"/>
    <prereq message="Turn Undead required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[~ If our hero does not have the Turn Undead tag we are not valid, else go check Class Helpers for Mystic & Cleric and determine if it has a cClrNeutGE field value of 0, if so then we are valid. We are also valid if we have 4 levels of Paladin and the Class Special is showing.

   doneif (hero.tagis[Hero.TurnUndead] = 0)

   validif (hero.childfound[cHelpClr].field[cClrNeutGE].value = 0)
   validif (hero.childfound[cHelpMys].field[cClrTurn].value = 2)
   validif (hero.childfound[cPalTurnUn].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0)]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fStitFlFam" name="Stitched Flesh Familiar" description="When you are ready and able to acquire a new familiar, you may choose to gain a stitched flesh familiar.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Ability to acquire a new familiar, ability to cast three or more necromancy spells.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When choosing a familiar, you may choose a stitched flesh familiar.\n\nA stitched flesh familiar appears similar to any of the standard familiars available in the Player&#146;s Handbook, except that the stitched flesh familiar is obviously sewn together from many different creatures of that kind and, to a practiced eye, is clearly an undead creature.\n\nA stitched flesh familiar is magically linked to its master in the same way as a normal familiar. A stitched flesh familiar uses the basic statistics for a creature of its kind, as given in the Monster Manual, except as noted below.\n\n{i}Hit Dice{/i}: A stitched flesh familiar has a d12 Hit Die and gains no bonus hit points from Constitution (since it is an undead creature). For effects that depend upon Hit Dice, use the master&#146;s character level or the familiar&#146;s normal Hit Dice total, whichever is higher.\n\n{i}Hit Points{/i}: Use 1/2 the master&#146;s total or the familiar&#146;s normal total, whichever is higher.\n\n{i}Attacks{/i}: Use the master&#146;s base attack bonus or the familiar&#146;s, whichever is higher.\n\n{i}Saving Throws{/i}: For each saving throw, use either the familiar&#146;s base save bonus or the master&#146;s (as calculated from his character level), whichever is higher.\n\n{i}Familiar Special Abilities{/i}: Use the second table in the Familiars sidebar on page 52 of the Player&#146;s Handbook to determine additional abilities, just as you would for a normal familiar. Stitched flesh familiars do not grant their masters any of the benefits that appear on the first table in that sidebar. Instead of the noted special ability, a stitched flesh familiar grants its master the ability to control 4 more Hit Dice of undead than he is normally capable of controlling (both through the rebuke undead ability and through spells such as {i}animate dead{/i})." compset="Feat" summary="Gain undead version of familiar, can control +4 HD of undead." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Ability to select an Arcane Familiar required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[CompAvail.cArcFamil] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTombBFort" name="Tomb-Born Fortitude" description="The power of undeath taints you, body and soul. Its power has hardened your flesh and given it the foul look of the grave.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Non good alignment, Tomb-Tainted Soul.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You have a 25% chance to resist critical hits. When a critical hit or sneak attack is scored against you, there is a 25% chance that the critical hit or sneak attack is negated and damage is instead rolled normally.\n\nIn addition, you do not risk death from massive damage. Your skin takes on the pallor and texture of a dead creature of your race." compset="Feat" summary="Gain 25% chance crit/sneak att is negated &amp; Imm to massive damage." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Tomb-Tainted Soul required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fTombTSoul] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Non-good alignment required.">tagis[Alignment.Good] = 0</exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTombBResi" name="Tomb-Born Resilience" description="The power of undeath taints you, deadening your mind and body to the effects of mind controlling magic, poison, and disease.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Non good alignment, Tomb-Tainted Soul.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain a +2 bonus on saving throws made to resist mind-affecting spells and abilities, poison, and disease.\n\nYour nails or claws grow yellow and rotten. Although this change has no effect on the damage of your unarmed or natural attacks, most individuals find such creatures horrid-looking." compset="Feat" summary="+2 bonus to saves vs poison, disease, &amp; mind affecting spells/abilities." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Tomb-Tainted Soul required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fTombTSoul] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Non-good alignment required.">tagis[Alignment.Good] = 0</exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTombBVita" name="Tomb-Born Vitality" description="The power of undeath taints you, body and soul. Its power has removed your need to sleep and eat.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Non good alignment, Tomb-Tainted Soul.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You do not need to sleep, and you are immune to magic sleep effects. If you are a spellcaster, you still require 8 hours of uninterrupted rest (but not sleep) to prepare your spells. In addition, you no longer need to eat.\n\nYour body grows unnaturally thin, your flesh stretching tightly over your bones to give you a freakish, skeletal appearance." compset="Feat" summary="No need to sleep or eat, immune to magic sleep effects." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Tomb-Tainted Soul required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fTombTSoul] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Non-good alignment required.">tagis[Alignment.Good] = 0</exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fTombTSoul" name="Tomb-Tainted Soul" description="Your soul is tainted by the foul touch of undeath.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Non good alignment.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You are healed by negative energy and harmed by positive energy as if you were an undead creature. This feat gives no other penalties or benefits of the undead type." compset="Feat" summary="Negative energy heals and positive energy harms, as though undead." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Non-good alignment required.">tagis[Alignment.Good] = 0</exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fUndLeader" name="Undead Leadership" description="You gain the service of loyal undead followers.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Character level 6th, non good alignment, Knowledge (religion) 1 rank.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You attract followers and a cohort as if you had taken the Leadership feat. Your leadership score is treated as 2 higher than it otherwise would be for the purposes of attracting undead followers and treated as 4 lower than it otherwise would be for the purposes of attracting living followers.\n\nIf you choose to attract an undead cohort rather than a living cohort, you can attract an undead cohort with a maximum effective character level equal to two less than your ECL. See page 106 of the Dungeon Master&#146;s Guide for more information on the Leadership feat.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: Like the standard Leadership feat, you must check with your DM before selecting this feat, and work with your DM to determine an appropriate cohort and followers for your character. See the Undead Cohorts and Followers section, below, for more information on choosing an undead creature as a cohort or follower." compset="Feat" summary="Gain cohort/followers, +2 to leadership score for undead, -4 for others." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Non-good alignment required.">tagis[Alignment.Good] = 0</exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Character level 6th required."><![CDATA[herofield[tLevel].value >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (religion) 1 rank required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kKnowRel] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fUnquFlLif" name="Unquenchable Flame of Life" description="You are hardened to the attacks of the undead.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You gain a +2 bonus on all saves against the extraordinary or supernatural abilities of undead creatures.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If you have selected undead as your favored enemy, your bonus on saving throws is instead equal to your favored enemy bonus against undead." compset="Feat" summary="+2 to saves vs extraordinary and supernatural abilities of undead." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fVamHunter" name="Vampire Hunter" description="Your knowledge of vampires has given you the extraordinary ability to detect subtle signs of their presence and to resist their dominating gaze ability.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Knowledge (religion) 6 ranks.\n\n{b}Benefits{/b}: You can take a move action to unfailingly determine whether a vampire or vampire spawn is within 30 feet of you. In addition, you are immune to the dominating gaze ability of vampires and vampire spawn." compset="Feat" summary="Move, know if vampire is in 30 ft, immune to vampire&apos;s dominating gaze." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LMort"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec" name="ShowSpec" abbrev="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (religion) 6 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kKnowRel] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
